children.subject: I'm only taking 8 tech units this semester as a junior and I was fine so you should be fine. I know you aren't allowed to P/NP EECS courses before you finish your EECS requirements though

history.content: I'm currently in 12 graded units + 3 P/NP units but I'm looking to change the grading option to P/NP for one of my non-technical humanities courses, which would leave me at 8 graded units  (2 technicals) and 7 P/NP units. Is this allowed for a non-graduating, non-senior (to be in such and such number of graded and P/NP units in one semester)? I'm an EECS major, for reference.
history.subject: Minimum number of graded units needed per semester?
